Bench Press - Barbell - Decline - Narrow- Grip
Instructions: Lie supline (face-up) on a declied bench with the barbell in a rack at eye-line and feet planted flat on the ground with bent knees. Grasp the barbell with a pronated (over-hand) grip just inside shoulder width. Dismount the barbell from the rack slowly until inline with the shoulder joint and hold with extended elbows. Lower the barbell slowly to the lower portion of the sernum. Press the bar upward until arms are extended.
